## 2. Phase 0: Prerequisites & Accounts

### 2.1 Accounts You Need

Set up these accounts BEFORE you start:

| Service | Purpose | Free Tier | Sign Up |
|---------|---------|-----------|---------|
| **GitHub** | Code hosting, CI/CD | Unlimited public repos | [github.com](https://github.com) |
| **Vercel** | Frontend hosting | 100 GB bandwidth/mo | [vercel.com](https://vercel.com) |
| **Railway** | Backend + Docker hosting | $5 trial credit | [railway.app](https://railway.app) |
| **Supabase** | PostgreSQL database | 500 MB DB, 2 projects | [supabase.com](https://supabase.com) |
| **Docker Hub** | Container registry (optional) | 1 private repo | [hub.docker.com](https://hub.docker.com) |

### 2.2 Tools You Need Installed Locally

```bash
# ── Essential ────────────────────────────────────
git --version          # Git (version control)
node --version         # Node.js (for frontend builds)
npm --version          # npm (JS package manager)
python --version       # Python 3.9+ (for backend)
pip --version          # pip (Python package manager)

# ── Recommended ──────────────────────────────────
docker --version       # Docker (for containerization)
docker compose version # Docker Compose (for local orchestration)

# ── Optional (for specific platforms) ────────────
railway --version      # Railway CLI
vercel --version       # Vercel CLI
```

### 2.3 Install Platform CLIs

```bash
# Railway CLI
npm install -g @railway/cli
railway login

# Vercel CLI
npm install -g vercel
vercel login

# Or use npm in specific commands with npx:
npx vercel deploy
```

