## 10. Phase 8: Frontend Deployment (Vercel)

### 10.1 Vercel Deployment Flow

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Push to GitHub] --> B[Vercel detects change]
    B --> C[npm install]
    C --> D[npm run build]
    D --> E[Upload dist/ to CDN]
    E --> F[Available globally via HTTPS]
```

### 10.2 Step-by-Step

**Step 1: Connect to Vercel**
```
1. vercel.com/new
2. Import your GitHub repo
3. Set Root Directory: frontend/ (or Frontend/)
```

**Step 2: Configure Build**
```
Framework Preset:    Vite (auto-detected)
Build Command:       npm run build
Output Directory:    dist
Install Command:     npm install
Node.js Version:     18.x or 20.x
```

**Step 3: Add Environment Variables**
```
VITE_API_BASE_URL = https://your-backend.railway.app
```

**Step 4: Deploy**
- Click "Deploy"
- Wait 1–2 minutes
- Get your URL: `https://your-app.vercel.app`

### 10.3 Custom Domain Setup

```
1. Vercel Dashboard → Project → Settings → Domains
2. Add: app.yourdomain.com
3. Add DNS records at your registrar:
   Type: CNAME
   Name: app
   Value: cname.vercel-dns.com
4. Wait for DNS propagation (5–60 min)
```

