## 13. Phase 11: Security Hardening

### 13.1 Security Checklist

| # | Item | Priority | How to Check |
|---|------|----------|-------------|
| 1 | No secrets in Git | 🔴 Critical | `grep -rn "password\|secret\|api_key" .` |
| 2 | CORS locked to specific origins | 🔴 Critical | Check `allow_origins` in app code |
| 3 | HTTPS everywhere | 🔴 Critical | Vercel/Railway auto-provide this |
| 4 | Input validation on all endpoints | 🟡 High | Review all API endpoints |
| 5 | File upload size limits | 🟡 High | Check FastAPI UploadFile config |
| 6 | Rate limiting | 🟡 High | Use `slowapi` or platform-level |
| 7 | Error messages don't leak internals | 🟡 High | No stack traces in production |
| 8 | Database access scoped (RLS) | 🟡 High | Check Supabase RLS policies |
| 9 | Dependencies up to date | 🟢 Medium | `pip audit` / `npm audit` |
| 10 | Logging doesn't contain secrets | 🟢 Medium | Review all `logger.*` calls |

### 13.2 CORS Configuration

```python
# ❌ BAD — allows any website to call your API
allow_origins=["*"]

# ✅ GOOD — only your frontend can call your API
allow_origins=["https://myapp.vercel.app", "https://myapp.com"]

# ✅ BEST — configurable via env var
allow_origins=os.environ.get("ALLOWED_ORIGINS", "http://localhost:5173").split(",")
```

### 13.3 Rate Limiting

```python
from slowapi import Limiter, _rate_limit_exceeded_handler
from slowapi.util import get_remote_address

limiter = Limiter(key_func=get_remote_address)
app.state.limiter = limiter

@app.post("/api/analyze")
@limiter.limit("10/minute")
async def analyze(request: Request, file: UploadFile):
    ...
```

### 13.4 File Upload Security

```python
# Maximum upload sizes
MAX_IMAGE_SIZE = 10 * 1024 * 1024   # 10 MB
MAX_PDF_SIZE = 20 * 1024 * 1024     # 20 MB
ALLOWED_IMAGE_TYPES = {"image/jpeg", "image/png", "image/webp"}
ALLOWED_PDF_TYPES = {"application/pdf"}

@app.post("/api/upload")
async def upload(file: UploadFile):
    # Check content type
    if file.content_type not in ALLOWED_IMAGE_TYPES:
        raise HTTPException(400, "Invalid file type")

    # Check file size
    contents = await file.read()
    if len(contents) > MAX_IMAGE_SIZE:
        raise HTTPException(400, "File too large (max 10 MB)")

    await file.seek(0)  # Reset for downstream use
    ...
```

