## 16. Phase 14: Scaling & Performance

### 16.1 When to Scale

| Symptom | Likely Cause | Solution |
|---------|-------------|----------|
| Slow API responses | ML model inference time | GPU backend, or async queue |
| Server crashes | Out of memory (OOM) | Increase RAM, optimize model |
| 502/503 errors | Too many concurrent requests | Scale horizontally (more instances) |
| Cold start lag | Container starting up | Keep-alive pings, pre-warm |

### 16.2 CPU vs GPU for ML Inference

| Metric | CPU | GPU |
|--------|-----|-----|
| Cost | $5–20/mo | $50–500/mo |
| Inference speed | 2–10 seconds per image | 0.1–1 second per image |
| Best for | Prototypes, low traffic | Production, high traffic |
| Providers | Railway, Render, Fly.io | RunPod, Modal, Lambda Cloud |

### 16.3 Async Processing for Heavy ML Tasks

```python
from fastapi import BackgroundTasks

@app.post("/api/analyze")
async def analyze(file: UploadFile, background_tasks: BackgroundTasks):
    # Quick response — don't make the user wait
    request_id = str(uuid.uuid4())

    # Run heavy ML inference in background
    background_tasks.add_task(run_ml_pipeline, request_id, file)

    return {"request_id": request_id, "status": "processing"}

@app.get("/api/results/{request_id}")
async def get_results(request_id: str):
    # Client polls this endpoint until results are ready
    ...
```

---

## 17. Phase 15: Cost Management

### 17.1 Free Tier Limits

| Service | Free Tier | Limits |
|---------|-----------|--------|
| **Vercel** | Hobby | 100 GB bandwidth, 100 deployments/day |
| **Railway** | Trial | $5 credit (one-time), then $5/mo Hobby |
| **Supabase** | Free | 500 MB DB, 1 GB file storage, 2 projects |
| **Pinata** | Free | 100 files, 1 GB storage |
| **GitHub** | Free | Unlimited repos, 500 MB LFS |

### 17.2 Estimated Monthly Costs

| Setup | Cost | Good For |
|-------|------|----------|
| **Hobby** | $5–15/mo | Side projects, demos, portfolios |
| **Starter** | $20–50/mo | Small production apps |
| **Production** | $50–200/mo | Real users, SLAs, GPU inference |
| **Scale** | $200+/mo | High traffic, multiple services |

### 17.3 Cost Optimization Tips

1. **Use CPU-only PyTorch** in Docker (`--index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu`) — saves 1.5 GB image size
2. **Sleep unused services** — Railway charges per hour of runtime
3. **Use Cloudflare R2** instead of S3 — no egress fees
4. **Cache model downloads** — use volumes instead of downloading every restart
5. **Pick the closest region** — reduces latency and bandwidth costs

---

## 18. Common Errors & Troubleshooting

### 18.1 Build Errors

| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'xyz'` | Missing from requirements.txt | Add `xyz` to requirements.txt |
| `ERROR: Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement torch==2.1.0+cu118` | CUDA version not available on CPU-only platform | Use `--index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu` |
| `"OSError: libGL.so.1: cannot open shared object file"` | OpenCV needs system libraries | Add `libgl1-mesa-glx` to Dockerfile apt-get |
| `"error: subprocess-exited-with-error"` during pip install | C extension compilation failed | Use `-headless` variant of package (e.g., `opencv-python-headless`) |

### 18.2 Runtime Errors

| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `CORS error` in browser console | Backend doesn't allow frontend origin | Add frontend URL to `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` |
| `fetch failed` / `ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED` | Wrong API URL or backend is down | Check `VITE_API_BASE_URL` and backend health |
| `413 Request Entity Too Large` | Upload exceeds nginx/platform limit | Increase upload limit in platform settings |
| `OOMKilled` / container crashes | Model too large for available RAM | Increase RAM allocation or use smaller model |
| `ModuleNotFoundError` at runtime (not build) | Missing optional dependency | Add try/except or add to requirements.txt |

### 18.3 Database Errors

| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `relation "xxx" does not exist` | Table not created | Run migration SQL in Supabase |
| `permission denied for table xxx` | RLS policy blocking access | Check/update RLS policies |
| `23505: duplicate key value violates unique constraint` | Inserting duplicate data | Add upsert logic or check before insert |

---

## 19. Universal Pre-Deployment Checklist

### 🔒 Security
- [ ] No secrets in Git (check `git log -p` for history)
- [ ] `.env` is in `.gitignore`
- [ ] `.env.example` exists with placeholder values
- [ ] CORS locked to specific origins (not `*`)
- [ ] All API keys rotated if ever committed
- [ ] File upload size limits configured
- [ ] Error responses don't leak stack traces

### 📦 Dependencies
- [ ] Every Python import has a matching requirements.txt entry
- [ ] `pip install -r requirements.txt` works on a fresh venv
- [ ] `npm install && npm run build` works for frontend
- [ ] No OS-specific dependencies (e.g., Windows-only packages)

### 🐳 Docker
- [ ] Dockerfile exists and builds successfully
- [ ] .dockerignore exists (excludes .git, .venv, node_modules, tests)
- [ ] Docker image size is reasonable (< 5 GB for ML, < 500 MB for non-ML)
- [ ] Health check endpoint exists (`/api/health` or `/health`)
- [ ] Container runs correctly: `docker run -p 8000:8000 --env-file .env my-app`

### ⚙️ Configuration
- [ ] All hardcoded paths are configurable via env vars
- [ ] All external service URLs are configurable via env vars
- [ ] Model paths are configurable via env vars
- [ ] Default values work for local development
- [ ] `railway.toml` or `render.yaml` exists

### 🗄️ Database
- [ ] Migration SQL files exist under version control
- [ ] All tables created in production database
- [ ] Connection uses env vars (not hardcoded credentials)
- [ ] RLS policies configured (if using Supabase)

### 🧪 Testing
- [ ] Backend health check returns 200
- [ ] At least one API endpoint tested with curl
- [ ] Frontend builds without errors
- [ ] Frontend → Backend connection works end-to-end

### 🚀 Deployment
- [ ] Backend deployed and health check passes
- [ ] Frontend deployed and loads correctly
- [ ] Environment variables set on all platforms
- [ ] CORS configured with production frontend URL
- [ ] DNS / custom domain configured (if applicable)

---

## 20. Platform Comparison Cheat Sheet

### Backend Hosting

| Feature | Railway | Render | Fly.io | AWS EC2 |
|---------|---------|--------|--------|---------|
| **Difficulty** | Easy | Easy | Medium | Hard |
| **Docker support** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Free tier** | $5 credit | 750 hrs/mo | 3 shared VMs | 12 months free |
| **Auto-deploy** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ (needs CI) |
| **Volumes** | ✅ | ✅ Disk | ✅ Volumes | ✅ EBS |
| **GPU** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ (A100) | ✅ (any GPU) |
| **Custom domain** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Sleep on idle** | Hobby plan sleeps | Free tier sleeps | ❌ | ❌ |
| **Best for** | ML backends, APIs | Simple APIs | Edge computing | Full control |

### Frontend Hosting

| Feature | Vercel | Netlify | Cloudflare Pages |
|---------|--------|---------|-----------------|
| **Difficulty** | Very Easy | Very Easy | Easy |
| **Framework support** | Vite, Next, React | Vite, React, Vue | Vite, React, Vue |
| **Free tier** | 100 GB/mo | 100 GB/mo | Unlimited |
| **Build time** | Fast | Fast | Fast |
| **Edge functions** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ (Workers) |
| **Custom domain** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Best for** | React/Next.js | Jamstack/static | Budget/speed |

### Database

| Feature | Supabase | Neon | PlanetScale | RDS |
|---------|----------|------|-------------|-----|
| **Engine** | PostgreSQL | PostgreSQL | MySQL | Any |
| **Free tier** | 500 MB | 512 MB | 5 GB | 12 months |
| **Auth built-in** | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |
| **REST API** | ✅ (auto) | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |
| **Realtime** | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |
| **Best for** | Full-stack apps | Serverless | High scale | Enterprise |

