## Quick Reference: The Deployment Order

```
 1.  📋  Audit: Check for secrets, missing deps, large files
 2.  🔒  Secrets: Move ALL secrets to .env, add .env.example
 3.  📦  Dependencies: Verify requirements.txt / package.json complete
 4.  🐳  Docker: Create Dockerfile + .dockerignore
 5.  🧪  Test Locally: docker build + docker run + curl /health
 6.  🗄️  Database: Create tables, test connection
 7.  🚂  Deploy Backend: Push to Railway/Render
 8.  ✅  Verify Backend: curl /api/health on production URL
 9.  ▲   Deploy Frontend: Push to Vercel/Netlify
10.  🔗  Connect: Set VITE_API_BASE_URL + ALLOWED_ORIGINS
11.  🎯  E2E Test: Full user flow on production
12.  📊  Monitor: Set up logging + alerts
```

---

> [!TIP]
> **Bookmark this guide.** Every time you start a new project or help a teammate deploy, come back to this checklist. Deployment mistakes are expensive — prevention is free.
